aveyard, 107P, 133P, 2006 VW139, D/1891 W1 Blanpain and 3200 Phaeton. Thus we\npropose that the asteroidal belt contains an enormous graveyard of ancient\ndormant and extinct rocky comets, that turn on (are rejuvenated), in response\nto a diminution of their perihelion distance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 May 2013 19:09:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 May 2013 22:16:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 7 Aug 2013 22:14:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
